My shaman is now 6 and has not finished the part to make the container for Merchant. Why? Because you need brewing skill ( at 10 points I finally managed to make the 2 sweet water but they were not trivial), you need  pottery skill ( I have failed 8 times trying to make the pottery part so far, including twice at the firing part).<br>
<br>
I twinked my cat with leather armor and  a fine steel Mace also about 20 PP. which means I had what I needed to raise my brewing skill to 10 before I even tried to make sweet water. Which saved me a lot of Xakra bile for the second part.<br>
<br>
The dogged insistance by you and others that these LOW level CLASS and RACE specific quests are not affected in a nearly undoable way by TLC (notice I didnt say impossible, since they are doable, of course making love to an elephant is doable to, but I wouldnt want to try) is a red herring. <br>
<br>
I killed Xakra larvae in the pit (only hunted in the pit). I killed the beetles in the pit ( I paid for the hairless hopper hides by the way) I had to kill skeletons in the pit when they attacked me. And I killed (finally at 3 and above though tough at 3) Scorpions. I managed to find 12 Xakra Bile and 13 Scorpion blood (all no drop, so effected by TLC) You need both. plus water to try and make sweet water BY 6th level 90 percent or more of the non scorpions are light blue. Meaning effected by TLC, since Light blue at 5 and 6 give NO experience ( a requirement to get items effected by TLC).<br>
<br>
What is my point?  The MAJORITY of new players will NOT be able to do these quests because TLC will be involved at lvl 5 and above. Unless of course you think every newbie has access to 20 PP (never mind the armor and weapon they arent that important , though do effect survival). <br>
<br>
Now I agree if you wait untill someone posts all the ways to do the quest ahead of time AND you avoid all the skeletons AND you get lucky at brewing and pottery AND you get lucky with the rare drops AND you group with NO ONE  AND you put off the acyrlia quest till absolutely neccassary for the quest (it raises you to almost 2 and is required just to get the quests started) AND you wait for the ground spawn on the mud AND you put 10 points of your training in Brewing AND you put 10 Points (though even at 10 I fail every attempt ) in Pottery (a skill I might add you are NOT warned you need ) AND somehow you get the needed cash (without hunting any mobs but the quest mobs) to buy the water (needed for brewing and for pottery) and for the firing sheets (needed for pottery) you might succeed at getting the container made, but I havent found out what the next step is, nor what other potentially trivial mobs (at 6 mind you) I still have to kill for quest stuff.<br>
<br>
Dont come here and claim that TLC when it effects such low level, class and race specific quests fosters ANYTHING good. The Vah Shir quests are examples of WHY TLC needs to be tweeked, but it wont ever be cause it was abandoned. <br>
<br>
