<br>
Plat for newbies on Luclin:  All over the place in Shadeweavers.  Kill hoppers.  The higher level ones drop claws which can sell for as much as 3 plat.  Chitterlings are a bit tougher, and require a magic weapon (do your quests and you'll get one, or kill poachers for one) but they uncommonly drop 'glowing chitterling wing' which sells for over a plat.  Go into the first cavern of Paludal out of Shadeweavers and collect mushrooms.  They're ground spawn and sell for 2 gold plus to the vendors.  and they stack.  Kill hoppers for scales and either sell them or turn them in for armor.  Skeletal Hunters drop up to a plat (got a plat off one already).  All the lesser shades drop shadowsilk commonly, which you can use to make shadesilk armor.<br>
<br>
The newbie quests are hard.  No doubting that.  But you only need to do them if you want to run the Sonic Wolf Bane weapons.  You can run the other quests in Shadeweavers to make seriously NICE armor (better than any other newbie armor out there) and incredible newbie weapons.<br>
<br>
Luclin zones are about quests.  Don't want to do the newbie ones?  You don't have to.  There are still incredible items to be acquired via quests in Shadeweavers.  There are more quests to be had in Hollowshade which haven't even been found yet.<br>
<br>
TLC makes it tough but not impossible. <p>Denoi Fishwhiskers<BR>
