A good guild (and, I'm looking for one, I'm not happy with my present one at all) will host language fairs (mine does, for that matter. If you haven't gotten to excellent in another language by level 20, your doing something wrong. I got to very good in Elvish in the Warrens simply by grouping with any elf I saw. <br>
<br>
But, thats just one example. What you describe is merely frustrating, its not broken. <br>
<br>
I do think that the TLC needs tweaking. Has it broken any quests? I haven't seen any examples given yet of a broken quest. <br>
<br>
I got a barnacle breastplate at level 11. To get that, you have to kill a diseased shark (blue at 11), then loot an item affected by the TLC. When the shark dies, it spawns around 4 tiny sharks, which also drop an item affected by the Trivial Loot code - and you have to be level 5 or below to get those items! Is this quest broken by the TLC? Course not. I just hired a level 4 (had to go to qeynos to get him) and had him kill the tiny sharks for me. <br>
<br>
I am going to do this quest again - even though the shark is now green to me. I'll simply have to hire a level 11, and a level 4. It only took me about 4 days to find a level four willing to do the job last time. Broke? No. Difficult? Yes. <br>
<br>
Your example with Word is spot on. Under normal circumstances, that page numbering is broke. Under the rules of FV - which are abundantly clear on their web site, it isn't, because you have a clear work around (manually numbering the pages.). Sure its more work, but thats the point of FV - to make the game more challenging, and thus more fun.<br>
